Daily Note

1.
Enumerator is a class using lazy loading concpet
which will do things only when what it is going to do and the scope of work

2.
When using block with parameter, you can assign default value to parameter
e.g.
  (1..10).each {|n, sum=0| sum = sum + n }
  # but sum will be throw away every time executed
  # and build up again every next time

3.
String, Integer, TrueClass, FalseClass & NilClass are classes without attr_writter

